# shadcn/ui Components — MANDATORY UI LIBRARY

This project uses [shadcn/ui](https://ui.shadcn.com/) as the **only** UI component library.

## Absolute Rules

- **NEVER** create custom UI components from scratch (no raw `<div>` styled buttons, custom modals, hand-rolled form inputs, etc.)
- **ALWAYS** use a shadcn/ui component if one exists for the use case
- **NEVER** use any other component library (MUI, Chakra, Radix primitives directly, Headless UI, etc.)
- If a shadcn/ui component does not exist for a specific use case, compose it from existing shadcn/ui primitives

## Clerk Authentication UI

- **All** Clerk sign-in and sign-up trigger buttons **must** use the shadcn/ui `<Button>` component — never Clerk's built-in `<SignInButton>` or `<SignUpButton>` rendered with default styling
- Clerk **must** be configured to use **modal mode** for sign-in and sign-up — never redirect to a separate page

```tsx
// ✅ GOOD — shadcn Button triggers Clerk modal
import { SignInButton, SignUpButton } from '@clerk/nextjs';
import { Button } from '@/components/ui/button';

<SignInButton mode="modal">
  <Button variant="outline">Sign In</Button>
</SignInButton>

<SignUpButton mode="modal">
  <Button>Get Started</Button>
</SignUpButton>

// ❌ BAD — Clerk default button with no shadcn wrapper
<SignInButton />

// ❌ BAD — redirect mode instead of modal
<SignInButton mode="redirect">...</SignInButton>
```

## Installing a Component

Components are **not bundled** — each must be installed individually into `src/components/ui/`.

```bash
npx shadcn@latest add <component-name>
```

### Examples

```bash
npx shadcn@latest add button
npx shadcn@latest add card
npx shadcn@latest add input
npx shadcn@latest add dialog
npx shadcn@latest add badge
```

Multiple components at once:

```bash
npx shadcn@latest add button card input dialog
```

## Checking Installed Components

Installed components live in `src/components/ui/`. Always check there before installing a new one.

## Usage

```tsx
import { Button } from "@/components/ui/button"

<Button variant="outline">Click me</Button>
```
